title: Remembrance Sri Lanka
description: The memorial for all Sri Lankans who were killed, forced to die, or forcibly disappeared due to state-sponsored crimes and direct socioeconomic and political reasons.

names.name: K.B. Chaminda Lakshan
names.description: Killed by police gunfire during a protest at Rambukkana against Rajapaksha regime

names.name: Dharmeratnam Sivaram (Taraki)
names.incident: He was kidnapped by four men in a white van on 28 April 2005, in front of the Bambalapitya police station. His body was found the next day in the district of Himbulala, near the Parliament of Sri Lanka. He had been beaten and shot in the head.

names.name: Mylvaganam Nimalrajan
names.incident: Shot dead by gunmen belonging to the paramilitary EPDP in the Sri Lanka Army's high security zone during a curfew

names.name: Prageeth Eknaligoda
names.incident: He was reported missing on January 24, 2010 - two days before the presidential polls in Sri Lanka when the island was under the Presidency of Mahinda Rajapakse - and has not been seen since
